          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Hollywood, CA</p>
  <h1>GUI Desktop Application Programmer (Cocoa or Winforms/WPF)</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>We’re a small, focused startup about to come out of closed Beta making a killer desktop app for the music industry.  Think Dropbox + Lightroom + YouSendIt.</p>

<p>We’re looking for someone who is passionate about building user interfaces &ndash; Mac or PC.  We’ve built the core of our Mac application &ndash; but there’s a lot of polish work to be done, and tons of features to add.  And we need someone who is also capable of spearheading efforts to build the UI for our Windows client.  You should have plenty of experience with either Mac or PC UI systems (Cocoa or WPF/Winforms), in a higher level language like Objective-C or C#, and be comfortable with C++ (since your code will be communicating with the core, cross-platform part of our app).</p>

<p>We’re still in beta, so you’ll be able to get in at the ground floor and have a real impact.  In the long run, we’re looking for someone who can grow into a role responsible for all of our client apps &ndash; Mac, PC, and eventually mobile. If this interests you, you’ll need to have a intuitive grasp of usability and an obsession with a great user experience.  And since our founders are extremely well-connected to the music industry, you might be getting feature requests directly from some of the biggest names in music.</p>

<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Experience building either Mac Applications using Objective-C / Cocoa or Windows Applications using WPF/WinForms and C#</li>
<li>Great knowledge of UI paradigms and tradeoffs</li>
<li>Comfortable with C++</li>
<li>Interested in learning about that ‘other &lt;evil/hippie> ui system’ &ndash; or prior experience with both</li>
</ul>


<p><strong>Pluses:</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Great aesthetic sense and usability experience</li>
<li>Mobile development experience</li>
</ul>


<p><strong> Please don&rsquo;t judge us by our placeholder website &ndash; it&rsquo;s all programmer art! Our designers are almost done with a new version that won&rsquo;t make your eyeballs bleed. </strong></p>
</div><!-- /.column.main -->

